===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[traffic]] [[light]]'''  (plural ''[[traffic lights]]'')
# a [[signalling]] [[device]] positioned at a [[road]] [[intersection]] or [[pedestrian crossing]] to indicate when it may be [[safe]] to drive, ride or walk, using a [[universal]] [[color code]].
#([[stamp-collecting]]) the coloured dots on stamp sheet [[margin]]s printed with [[offset litho]] or [[photogravure]] methods, used by the printers to check colour [[accuracy]].
